===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The [[height]] below a [[surface]]; the amount that something is [[deep]].
#: ''Measure the '''depth''' of the water in this part of the bay.''
# The distance between the front and the back, as the depth of a drawer or closet.
# {{context|figurative}} The [[intensity]], complexity, strength, seriousness or [[importance]] of an emotion, or situation.
#: ''The '''depth''' of her misery was apparent to everyone.''
#: ''The '''depth''' of the crisis had been exaggerated.''
# {{context|computing|colors}} The total [[palette]] of available [[color]]s.
# {{context|art|photography}} The property of appearing [[three-dimensional]].
#: ''The '''depth''' of field in this picture is amazing.''

